<br />
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Bid 1, if you win choose to go second. You want to make sure your site 3 comes up. If he makes you go first, single to second and encourage him (subtly) to double-move. <br />
Try not to play anything in the Fellowship phase. Remember that in the maneuevers you can play stuff on Eowyn and THeoden even if they are woundless or there&#39;s no allies out. THis ensures there&#39;s 3 pool out so Gandalf is +3, lets you use your Fury of the White Riders, and Deep in Thought. Kill or exhaust big guys ith Fury, finish them off with Rohirrim Bow. Sigewulf lets you double move, Hlafwine boosts Gamling, Theoden heals them both. The Wargs will slow your opponent down so you can get in the lead. If you manage to control a plains early and get Wolves on it, the game is over. Foul Horde with Sharku&#39;s Warg will add 2 twilight, put 4 wounds for the fights, then get out 5 more in the regroup! I always go for the Fellowship win, it&#39;s more reliable. It&#39;s pretty tight already, but if you have any suggestions please d-mail me or include them in your review.  <br />
Gamling kills people like heck, and Gandalf is a pretty reliable strength 12, damage +2 guy. Eowyn heals herself up, you can toss a bunch of Rohirrim Bows on her, she heals herself a phase before the exertion. The Household Guards are there for the 5 Valiants (Sigewulf) but I&#39;m hoping to change them out for Eomer and Aragorn perhaps, come Ents of Fangorn. (I&#39;ve heard they&#39;ll be Valiant)  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
